cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper deals with cross-domain collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model involves learning embeddings and capturing high-order feature interactions, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). The objective function is formulated as a ranking problem, which is a common approach in natural language processing (cs.CL).
